= About Me

~~~
{}{img_left}{ProfilePic.jpeg}{WHAT}{215px}{300}{}
Anthony Ostuni 

I am a PhD student in UC San Diego's [https://cstheory.ucsd.edu/home.html CS theory group],
where I am extremely fortuate to be advised by [https://cseweb.ucsd.edu/~dakane/ Daniel Kane] and 
[http://cseweb.ucsd.edu/~slovett/home.html Shachar Lovett]. I completed my undergraduate studies at the 
University of Maryland, College Park (UMD), receiving a BS in computer science and applied mathematics.

I've previously spent time as a researcher at UMD's [http://www.cs.umd.edu/projects/reucaar/ Combinatorics and 
Algorithms for Real Problems] REU program, as well as a 
software engineering intern at [https://careers.google.com/students/engineering-and-technical-internships/ Google] 
and the [https://www.jhuapl.edu/ Johns Hopkins Applied Physics Laboratory]. 
~~~

I currently co-run [https://cstheory.ucsd.edu/lunch.html UCSD Theory Lunch]. I have previously assisted with visit days.

== Research Interests

I am broadly interested in combinatorics and complexity. See [papers.html Writing] for my publications and other writing.

